<paragraph id="8BB21633CA62FFC6FEF6FCB9FC16FBDA" blockId="48.[264,1324,284,1110]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
Remarks. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9C6BC2CA62FFC6FE7EFCB9FDE7FCB2" author="Arrow, G. J." box="[432,594,804,830]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="153 - 157" refId="ref31219" refString="Arrow, G. J. (1910) On the lamellicorn beetles of the genus Peltonotus with descriptions of four new species. Annals and Magazine of Natural History (Series 8), 5, 153 - 157." type="journal article" year="1910">Arrow (1910)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D6DB0CA62FFC6FD1AFCB9FCFCFCB1" box="[724,841,804,829]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Peltonotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittatus">
<emphasis id="B979CA21CA62FFC6FD1AFCB9FCFCFCB1" box="[724,841,804,829]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">P. vittatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on a single female specimen with label data “ 
<collectingCountry id="F31A56A3CA62FFC6FE44FCD1FD80FCEA" box="[394,565,844,870]" name="Malaysia" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">North Borneo</collectingCountry>
.” Two specimens recorded from “Elopura” (
<collectingRegion id="49C9D8D1CA62FFC6FBF2FCD1FB7FFCEA" box="[1084,1226,844,870]" country="Malaysia" name="Sabah" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Sabah State</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F31A56A3CA62FFC6FB18FCD1FE9FFC02" name="Malaysia" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
) are of dubious validity because this locality is near sea level and probably does not possess suitable habitat for the species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D6DB0CA62FFC6FD39FC01FCC1FC39" box="[759,884,924,949]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Peltonotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B979CA21CA62FFC6FD39FC01FCC1FC39" box="[759,884,924,949]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Peltonotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Two specimens (housed at 
<collectionCode id="ED1C8EF6CA62FFC6FB02FC01FA97FC3A" box="[1228,1314,924,950]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">ZMHB</collectionCode>
) are labeled with an unknown locality: “Long Petak”. Limited label data for 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D6DB0CA62FFC6FB4EFC59FB47FC51" box="[1152,1266,964,989]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Peltonotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittatus">
<emphasis id="B979CA21CA62FFC6FB4EFC59FB47FC51" box="[1152,1266,964,989]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">P. vittatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
provide some indication that the species occurs in central Borneo and northern Borneo. Additional specimens will demonstrate whether populations of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D6DB0CA62FFC6FC22FB89FBD2FBA1" box="[1004,1127,1044,1069]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Peltonotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittatus">
<emphasis id="B979CA21CA62FFC6FC22FB89FBD2FBA1" box="[1004,1127,1044,1069]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">P. vittatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are contiguous throughout Borneo or if they are isolated geographically.
</paragraph>
